NAME
    passwd - update user's authentication tokens

SYNOPSIS
    passwd [username]

DESCRIPTION
    The passwd utility is used to update user's authentication token(s). If no username
    is apecified, the command refers to the currently logged in user.

CAVEATS
    Only users with root permission (gid 0) are allowed to change passwords of other users.

FILES
    /etc/passwd.json
        User account information.

SEE ALSO
    passwd, userdel, id, who.

